 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/boats-to-save-people/&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given a binary array  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt; , you should delete one element from it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;the size of the longest non-empty subarray containing only  &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt; &#39;s in the resulting array&lt;/em&gt;. Return  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;  if there is no such subarray.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: nums = [1,1,0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: 3&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: After deleting the number in position 2, [1,1,1] contains 3 numbers with value of 1&#39;s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: nums = [0,1,1,1,0,1,1,0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: 5&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: After deleting the number in position 4, [0,1,1,1,1,1,0,1] longest subarray with value of 1&#39;s is [1,1,1,1,1].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-3&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-3&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: nums = [1,1,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: 2&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: You must delete one element.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
