&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A condition, or &amp;quot;if-statement&amp;quot;, is something that is either  &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;  or  &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A condition is often a comparison &lt;strong&gt;check between two values&lt;/strong&gt; like in the example above to see if one value is greater than the other.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We use comparison operators like  &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt; ,  &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/code&gt;  or  &lt;code&gt;!==&lt;/code&gt;  to do such checks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparison checks can also be combined with logical operators such as  &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/code&gt;  or  &lt;code&gt;||&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
